{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6dd84cc2-4394-441f-a058-efa44d887768","content":"Yes, both are known MSTest v4 breaking changes. Here's the rundown:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Lost test history in Azure DevOps\n\nMSTest v4 changed the **test-ID algorithm**. Every test gets a new ID, so ADO treats them as brand-new. There is no opt-out — you'll keep the new history going forward.\n\n### 2. `TestContext.TestName` in `[ClassInitialize]`\n\nIn v4, the `TestContext` passed to `[ClassInitialize]` is a **class-level context** — it is not associated with any individual test. Accessing `TestName` (or other test-scoped properties) throws `InvalidOperationException`.\n\nYour fix — remove that access from `ClassInit`:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_vPU8UOIEZsAgolVuJ2UFuT","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-f84246417aa0405aa054059032f439a0/SetupTests.cs","old_str":"    [ClassInitialize]\n    public static void ClassInit(TestContext context)\n    {\n        var testName = context.TestName;\n        // Log setup for specific test\n    }","new_str":"    [ClassInitialize]\n    public static void ClassInit(TestContext context)\n    {\n        // In MSTest v4 the TestContext passed here is class-scoped;\n        // TestName is only available in [TestInitialize] or [TestMethod].\n    }"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-f84246417aa0405aa054059032f439a0/SetupTests.cs."}],"interactionId":"adbf37bb-4a2a-4c38-8dda-f8b9b1541184","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about MSTest v4 breaking changes. Let me provide what I know about MSTest v4 changes based on my knowledge, and also look at their specific code to give tailored advice.\n\nKey MSTest v4 breaking changes I know about:\n\n1. **Test ID calculation changed** — MSTest v4 changed how test IDs are computed (fully qualified names now include namespace by default, and the algorithm changed). This causes Azure DevOps / TRX test results to see them as entirely new tests, losing history.\n\n2. **TestContext in ClassInitialize** — In MSTest v4, the `TestContext` passed to `[ClassInitialize]` is no longer associated with any specific test method. \n\nAccessing `TestContext.TestName` during class initialization will now throw an `InvalidOperationException` since there's no active test at that point—this worked in v3 only by accident due to implementation details.\n\n3. **Other notable v4 breaking changes:**\n   - `DeploymentItem` attribute behavior changed\n   - `DataRow` attribute handling changes\n   - Parallel execution defaults may have changed\n   - `AssemblyInitialize`/`AssemblyCleanup` behavior changes\n   - `TestContext.Properties` is read-only in some contexts\n   - The `TestContext` passed to `[ClassInitialize]` is now a \"class-level\" context rather than test-specific\n\n, so it won't have test-level information available\n\nI should give them practical guidance on how to adapt their code to these v4 changes.","outputTokens":742,"requestId":"981A:23633C:1350C6D:1849164:69FFF5E5"},"id":"15dae4b0-0ae6-40cc-b993-dca26daf1853","timestamp":"2026-05-10T03:05:25.354Z","parentId":"8f8feec6-ab46-47ba-96fb-0d2f830cd8da"}
