{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4adf9fdd-c974-4ee4-b41b-1be43e055b3f","content":"If you need per-test logging, move it to `[TestInitialize]` where `TestContext` is test-scoped.\n\n### 3. Other v4 things to watch for\n\n| Area | Change |\n|---|---|\n| **Parallel execution** | Now enabled by default at the **method** level. Add `[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.ClassLevel)]` or `[assembly: DoNotParallelize]` if tests aren't thread-safe. |\n| **`TestContext.Properties`** | Read-only in class/assembly init contexts. |\n| **`Assert.AreEqual` on doubles** | Floating-point tolerance checks are stricter; explicitly pass a `delta`. |\n| **`[DeploymentItem]`** | Copy semantics changed; verify paths if you deploy test data files. |\n| **Timeout default** | `[Timeout]` now applies to test **method only** (not init/cleanup). Use `[Timeout]` on cleanup separately if needed. |\n\n**Recommended audit:** search for `TestContext.TestName` and `TestContext.Properties` in any `[ClassInitialize]` or `[AssemblyInitialize]` method — those are the most common runtime breaks.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"adbf37bb-4a2a-4c38-8dda-f8b9b1541184","outputTokens":286,"requestId":"981A:23633C:13531FC:184BFD9:69FFF5F5"},"id":"65ef248e-13d1-4e4b-9b2a-a9729bfa36a8","timestamp":"2026-05-10T03:05:33.450Z","parentId":"49a25a73-43e3-425a-93a6-43cb3c8e0f30"}
